<subSubSection id="1F2088EC1389A6A55A3A6B6881C599F0" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F4C7B91512E3043C6412CE630A822575" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A37355FF0F0217953911CE23FD20EA49" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">
This species is named in honour of Gill Stevens (
<normalizedToken id="DB385D75D23194D1FC637254DF91AD28" originalValue="née">nee</normalizedToken>
Douglas, born 1965), botanist, colleague and close friend who died during the preparation of this manuscript. Gill, an algologist by training, helped pioneer the use of amateur groups in the collection of biodiversity data in the UK.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF6F9A19F68415AF238734FF07DFF81D" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A9D02C26231C91FCCD34F8C001BF7AC4" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85E9686A28D254265B96FEA3355359C8" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="B0D30869727AC4009D7E7C255168BAD5" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="7A5504D3AC2636017D64FF1944E0F3A9" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from three cloud forest localities within the Cerro Pirre mountain range. Cerro Pirre covers an area of ca. 50 
<normalizedToken id="B590A4778832DCEF5E7A39894311F54C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
25 km. Using collection label data and 
<bibRefCitation id="FC580D7F0E968BD4E7F37080E0877F7F" author="Google Earth, 6.0.3.2197" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="25" pageNumber="74" refId="B7" refString="Google Earth, 6.0.3.2197, 2011. Available from http://www.google.com/earth." title="Available from http: // www. google. com / earth" year="2011">Google Earth</bibRefCitation>
(accesssed June 6, 2011; images from 2003) the Extent of Occurrence is calculated to be ca. 260 km2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9166D8C413C1DFB0DE638F3D7389ED5" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE664492641EC872BD693C94C1EF2557" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C6C5317EFBA9F9C7929403C18CA92F38" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">
Of the three collections of 
<taxonomicName id="248C6F6C1716F9E408D4CAB3510B108B" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="C65257F6DA690D41DF7CC114BFCE771B" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seen, only one had been previously determined to species, as 
<taxonomicName id="E09C5890C0AAF5DC3DB80FF90D14474E" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="langeanum">
<emphasis id="F2389A6C7476FF775D3E259E1987C0FE" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum langeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="7A8516774FDB2494A1B3631513D26BEE" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
. A comparison of the holotype and paratype material with type specimens from the herbaria listed in the Materials and methods section recovered 
<taxonomicName id="D41C36EB2A915FCDA110FBDEE54D395A" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="F39424821F9B5460259B6A64603C26F2" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0A1DD330CE576248EC2651480FD318DE" authorityName="A. T. Hunziker" authorityYear="1980" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="morae">
<emphasis id="AD5276504D2E2F6F890FCED40AC85D42" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum morae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hunz. and to a lesser extent 
<taxonomicName id="FF1772E8355F73833543C9B6EE8945EE" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="langeanum">
<emphasis id="FDE52EDB81C96F2BE3B075393593E931" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum langeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="C2494E42B7D6528F8F6137C3FCE453C1" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
(see Discussion for 
<taxonomicName id="F1E6E3CB18885AE028F39DA54EA973A8" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="3E64AE338B3F45E80868684A4F5B16B9" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above). For this reason 
<taxonomicName id="AF484946E7EEE5C962163E71EEB59DEB" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="FFAAB7444E27BB59468667AFB3CE1056" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is contrasted to both 
<taxonomicName id="80E5A13D0BD7C8DF19A686ABABD51CA0" authorityName="A. T. Hunziker" authorityYear="1980" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="morae">
<emphasis id="8E7866595C1AF3F72286207A7517C5E7" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum morae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28DB34FA6FB56A79A74EE5DDF79361A2" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="langeanum">
<emphasis id="079D1156C3855B361B23B697D5458FA8" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum langeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of habit and inflorescence and flower morphology as summarised in 
<tableCitation id="0522E6A3CA2C0D9413ACC42A309FBA37" captionStart="Table 7" captionStartId="T7" captionText="Table 7." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/235CB111466C4397FDD7DF0FEC154CD1" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" tableUuid="235CB111466C4397FDD7DF0FEC154CD1">Tables 7</tableCitation>
<tableCitation id="12C86B56286293808BC24CC876F72E27" captionStart="Table 8" captionStartId="T8" captionText="Table 8." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3FF7BB17BB062FEEC1A5E794A561EFE3" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" tableUuid="3FF7BB17BB062FEEC1A5E794A561EFE3">&amp; 8</tableCitation>
respectively.
</paragraph>
