<subSubSection id="E5DEA3E41C965C333E3521D0E59EB72E" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="2C0358FF90A945ADCFF1956E6E7C60A3" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="568AC413F921BFA89077A105D2ED168D" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">
Using IUCN criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="281AFD8DAA6A3BB3CA1A798A16E6109B" author="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival, Commission" journalOrPublisher="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge" pageId="25" pageNumber="74" refId="B9" refString="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival, Commission, 2001. IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge, 70 pp." title="IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="237FB20720228B375E7FA89C07C93402" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="C426D9A2F17882D07B167B7C77DB9AEF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered to be Near Threatened under 
<bibRefCitation id="83C2DC4A54DE6427421F0996569BCA99" author="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival, Commission" journalOrPublisher="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge" pageId="25" pageNumber="74" refId="B9" refString="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival, Commission, 2001. IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge, 70 pp." title="IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1." year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
criteria. The Extent of Occurrence is calculated to be ca. 260 km2 (Criteria B1, &lt;5,000km2) and there are only three known localities (Criteria B1a, ≤5). No decline in geographic range or fragmentation of the habitat has been observed and Cerro Pirre is located within the 
<normalizedToken id="C0226A365EC44EB00410CE59445C71FD" originalValue="Darién">Darien</normalizedToken>
Biosphere Reserve, a UNESCO World Heritage Property. The 
<normalizedToken id="B9D191537491300D6D32B094AF798FD6" originalValue="Darién">Darien</normalizedToken>
is, however, vulnerable to factors (see Conservation Status above for 
<taxonomicName id="4413AFE14992AF467F6B03A84A202EA0" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="E5DB52143A56C7248E9943646C8306D9" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and any decline in geographic range or fragmentation would result in this species being assessed as Endangered. For this reason 
<taxonomicName id="4F8066A0572A694D8FD9FAB75E4E6751" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="044FF5F6EFCF1067E88E62651DA442AF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered Near Threatened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
